  kind: python_call_eq
  category: identity
  id_prefix: iob3173

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [br_len_14,   BufferedReader.__name__.__len__,   [],  14, "io.BufferedReader.__name__.__len__() == 14 — 'BufferedReader' = 'Buffered'(8)+'Reader'(6) = 14; the three-way tie in name length (BufferedReader=BufferedWriter=BufferedRandom=14) arises from the uniform 'Buffered'(8) prefix and equal-length 6-character suffixes; 14 == 8 + 6 where 8 is len('Buffered') and 6 is the common suffix length for Reader, Writer, and Random; all three suffix words are exactly 6 characters: 'Reader'(6), 'Writer'(6), 'Random'(6); confirmed Python 3.14.3 macOS"]
    - [bw_len_14,   BufferedWriter.__name__.__len__,   [],  14, "io.BufferedWriter.__name__.__len__() == 14 — 'BufferedWriter' = 'Buffered'(8)+'Writer'(6) = 14; BufferedWriter (14) ties with BufferedReader (14) and BufferedRandom (14) in class name length; 'Writer' (6 chars) == 'Reader' (6 chars) == 'Random' (6 chars): a three-way suffix tie at 6 characters that propagates to the three-way class name tie at 14; BufferedWriter.__name__.__len__() (14) == BufferedReader.__name__.__len__() (14) == BufferedRandom.__name__.__len__() (14): confirmed identical lengths; confirmed Python 3.14.3 macOS"]
    - [bra_len_14,  BufferedRandom.__name__.__len__,   [],  14, "io.BufferedRandom.__name__.__len__() == 14 — 'BufferedRandom' = 'Buffered'(8)+'Random'(6) = 14; the three-way tie at 14 (BufferedReader, BufferedWriter, BufferedRandom) is the complete set of concrete buffered I/O classes in the io module; 14 == len('BufferedReader') == len('BufferedWriter') == len('BufferedRandom') — verified for all three; 14 also equals len('BufferedIOBase') — the public abstract base class name has the same length (14 chars: 'Buffered'(8)+'IO'(2)+'Base'(4)=14) as all three concrete subclasses; confirmed Python 3.14.3 macOS"]
    - [base_len_15, "BufferedReader.__bases__[0].__name__.__len__", [], 15, "io.BufferedReader.__bases__[0].__name__.__len__() == 15 — '_BufferedIOBase' has 15 characters: '_'(1)+'Buffered'(8)+'IO'(2)+'Base'(4) = 15; '_BufferedIOBase' (15 chars) is 1 character longer than each of the three concrete buffered classes (14 chars each) — the C-level base name is slightly longer due to the leading underscore; '_BufferedIOBase' (15 chars) == '_BufferedIOBase' for all three buffered classes: BufferedReader.__bases__[0].__name__ == BufferedWriter.__bases__[0].__name__ == BufferedRandom.__bases__[0].__name__ == '_BufferedIOBase'; confirmed Python 3.14.3 macOS"]
    - [mod_len_3,   BufferedReader.__module__.__len__, [], 3,  "io.BufferedReader.__module__.__len__() == 3 — '_io' has 3 characters: '_'(1)+'i'(1)+'o'(1) = 3; '_io' (3 chars) > 'io' (2 chars) by 1 — the C extension module name is one character longer than the public module name; all three buffered classes have __module__.__len__() == 3 — BufferedReader, BufferedWriter, and BufferedRandom all have the 3-character module '_io'; the module name '_io' (3 chars) is much shorter than any of the class names (14 chars) or the base class name (15 chars); confirmed Python 3.14.3 macOS"]

